The aim of the role is to assist suppliers in achieving the level of quality expectations by the company.The tasks of the Supplier Quality Lead (m/f) are as follows, but not limited to:
Working with suppliers to establish performance deliverables and parts readiness activities;
Ranking suppliers in a supplier development structure focusing on reduced costs and improved quality;
Evaluate potential suppliers together with purchasing;
Promote an improvement culture within the supplier base;
Conduct quality system audits and work with suppliers on non-conformance activities to ensure future compliance;
Provide assistance and guidance to suppliers to improve the performance of suppliers;
Assist the Quality Manager in monitoring the performance of all suppliers in relation to quality, delivery performance and cost;
Work with suppliers on non-conformance activities and ensure irreversible corrective actions have been implemented;
Assist in the development of Global SQD processes.

The Successful Applicant
The successful candidate will possess the following qualifications:
MSc or BSc in engineering;
At least 5 years of working experience in a quality assurance role preferably within the automotive manufacturing industry;
Experience in working with DFMEA, ISO & PPAP processes;
Experience in lean manufacturing
Sound knowledge of commercial practices, policies and negotiation;
Fluent English and Slovak language knowledge is mandatory;
Experience with working in an international environment;
Proactive, independent, creative, team-player and hands-on approach.

